Estate papers, 1819-1846, of Henry King (d. 1837) of
         Richmond, Virginia, consist of the will of Henry King; letters
         to King regarding sale of slaves; business papers of King;
         accounts kept by King's administrator Charles P. Goodall;
         receipts, including tax receipts to the King estate;
         promissory notes, bonds, and legal papers concerning the King
         estate.
